"title": "8319: perception, spiritual",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "8319: perception, spiritual",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The ability to see beneath the outward form to the underlying, often hidden, reality. It is a necessary gift in dealing with people, understanding spiritual teaching and interpreting events. Perception is important for effective service, though is often lacking, even among God's people.</p>\n<h2>Perception in dealing with people</h2>\n<h3>God's knowledge of human hearts</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps139:1-Ps139:4\">PSA 139:1–139:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps17:3\">PSA 17:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps44:21\">PSA 44:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov24:12\">PRO 24:12</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ's perception of those around him</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John2:24-John2:25\">JHN 2:24–2:25</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa11:1-Isa11:4\">ISA 11:1–11:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt9:3-Matt9:4\">MAT 9:3–9:4</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark2:7-Mark2:8\">MRK 2:7–2:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke5:21-Luke5:22\">LUK 5:21–5:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John4:16-John4:19\">JHN 4:16–4:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev2:23\">REV 2:23</a></p>\n<h3>True understanding by God's servants</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh6:1-Neh6:2\">NEH 6:1–6:2</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job21:27\">JOB 21:27</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts5:1-Acts5:3\">ACT 5:1–5:3</a></p>\n<h2>Perception of spiritual truth</h2>\n<h3>Recognising God's ultimate authority</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev4:1-Rev4:2\">REV 4:1–4:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs6:15-2Kgs6:17\">2KI 6:15–6:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan7:8-Dan7:14\">DAN 7:8–7:14</a></p>\n<h3>Understanding Jesus Christ's teaching</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt13:10-Matt13:11\">MAT 13:10–13:11</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark4:10-Mark4:11\">MRK 4:10–4:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke8:9-Luke8:10\">LUK 8:9–8:10</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt13:16-Matt13:23\">MAT 13:16–13:23</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark4:13-Mark4:20\">MRK 4:13–4:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke8:11-Luke8:15\">LUK 8:11–8:15</a> <em>The parable of the sower is about the way Jesus Christ's teaching in parables is received.</em></p>\n<h3>Understanding who Jesus Christ is</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt16:15-Matt16:17\">MAT 16:15–16:17</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark8:29\">MRK 8:29</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:20\">LUK 9:20</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts8:30-Acts8:35\">ACT 8:30–8:35</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa53:7-Isa53:8\">ISA 53:7–53:8</a></p>\n<h3>Understanding about Jesus Christ's death and resurrection</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke24:45-Luke24:46\">LUK 24:45–24:46</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke24:30-Luke24:35\">LUK 24:30–24:35</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John12:16\">JHN 12:16</a></p>\n<h2>Perception to interpret events</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam5:11-2Sam5:12\">2SA 5:11–5:12</a></strong> <em>The building of a palace in the newly captured Jerusalem confirms to David his election by God</em>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa43:9-Isa43:12\">ISA 43:9–43:12</a></strong> <em>Through his miraculous direction of his people's history, God is perceived as the one, true God.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa41:18-Isa41:20\">ISA 41:18–41:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa64:4\">ISA 64:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jonah1:12\">JON 1:12</a> <em>Jonah recognises God's hand in the storm</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts10:34-Acts10:35\">ACT 10:34–10:35</a> <em>Through the circumstances of his guidance, Peter realises that God's salvation is for Gentiles too.</em></p>\n<h2>Perception leading to effective service</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs3:9\">1KI 3:9</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr1:10\">2CH 1:10</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam16:7-1Sam16:13\">1SA 16:7–16:13</a> <em>Samuel perceives that David is to be king</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs4:8-2Kgs4:10\">2KI 4:8–4:10</a> <em>A Shunammite's perception of Elisha leads her to extend hospitality to him</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb11:27\">HEB 11:27</a> <em>Moses' perception of the invisible God</em></p>\n<h2>Lack of perception</h2>\n<h3>By those in the OT</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa43:19\">ISA 43:19</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod5:2\">EXO 5:2</a> <em>Pharaoh</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num22:31-Num22:34\">NUM 22:31–22:34</a> <em>Balaam</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut32:28-Deut32:29\">DEU 32:28–32:29</a> <em>Israel in the wilderness</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa29:10-Isa29:12\">ISA 29:10–29:12</a> <em>the people of Jerusalem</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa42:20\">ISA 42:20</a> <em>Israel</em></p>\n<h3>By some Jews in the NT</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt13:13-Matt13:15\">MAT 13:13–13:15</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark4:12\">MRK 4:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke8:10\">LUK 8:10</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa6:9-Isa6:10\">ISA 6:9–6:10</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke12:56\">LUK 12:56</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John3:3-John3:4\">JHN 3:3–3:4</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts28:26\">ACT 28:26</a></p>\n<h3>By Jesus Christ's disciples</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt15:16\">MAT 15:16</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark7:18\">MRK 7:18</a> <em>not understanding what makes a person unclean</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt16:9\">MAT 16:9</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark8:17-Mark8:18\">MRK 8:17–8:18</a> <em>not understanding about the teaching of the Pharisees and Sadducees</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt16:22\">MAT 16:22</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark8:32\">MRK 8:32</a> <em>Peter cannot accept that Jesus Christ must be crucified</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John14:9\">JHN 14:9</a> <em>Philip does not understand that Jesus Christ reveals the Father</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John20:9\">JHN 20:9</a> <em>not understanding about the resurrection</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John20:14\">JHN 20:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John21:4\">JHN 21:4</a></p>",
